Perimeter Defense - Email Security > [T2]: Secure Email Attachments: Whitelist allowed file types


Whitelist allowed file types.

Create a list of file types you expect your users to receive, configure your email gateway to allow attachment types you have whitelisted, and quarantine everything else. This way, we can reduce the attack surface significantly and ensure that only legit attachments are permitted.

 

Its essential to quarantine blocked emails with disallowed file types instead of dropping the mail. Sometimes, users receive legitimate emails with a blocked attachment type -false positive. Being able to restore those emails is crucial for business operations. In addition, blocked attachments are a great source of intel. SOC analysts can analyze and extract meaningful information about attackers' capabilities and intentions from blocked threats.

 

No 'one fits all list of legitimate file types all organizations can use. Every business has different needs. The best way to approach this control is to monitor incoming emails for 1-3 months, identify legitimate file types and build your list.

Here are the available attachment filtering options on Cisco ESA:

 

Figure - zoom in

 

As a start, you can allow the following types DOCUMENTS, IMAGES, and TEXT. This technique -aka whitelisting- is better than blacklisting (blocking specific files and letting everything else) because its pretty hard to keep track of new types that could be used maliciously.

 

Some organizations find it hard to take the whitelist approach because of their changing business needs. Depending on your situation, you may opt to go with a blacklist. A blacklist is easier to implement but less secure. On the contrary, a whitelist is harder to implement and maintain but offers better security. The whitelist must be very accurate; otherwise, legitimate emails will be blocked.
 

Sometimes the mail gateway in place may not have the option to filter based on file types. Security engineers may be forced to filter based on file extensions instead of file types in these situations. Here is a suggested list of file extensions to block or allow based on your preference.
